          <div class="sl-review-text">I've always struggled with people-pleasing. The exercises in this workbook helped me use my anger as a signal that a boundary was crossed, and taught me how to enforce it.</div>
          <div class="sl-review-helpful">👍 Helpful</div>
        </div>

        <div class="sl-review-card">
          <div class="sl-review-stars">★★★★★</div>
          <div class="sl-review-title">A completely different approach</div>
          <div class="sl-review-meta">Verified Reader &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span class="sl-verified">✓ Verified Purchase</span></div>
          <div class="sl-review-text">Most anger books just tell you to take deep breaths. This one actually digs into *why* women suppress anger and the cultural baggage behind it. Brilliant.</div>
          <div class="sl-review-helpful">👍 Helpful</div>
        </div>

        <div class="sl-review-card">
          <div class="sl-review-stars">★★★★★</div>
